      • searchMap

        @GET(value="/v1/autocomplete")
retrofit2.Call<MapzenPOJO> searchMap(@Query(value="api_key")
                                                                     java.lang.String api_key,
                                                                     @Query(value="focus.point.lat")
                                                                     double localizedLat,
                                                                     @Query(value="focus.point.lon")
                                                                     double localizedLng,
                                                                     @Query(value="text")
                                                                     java.lang.String searchQuery)
        Search Map with a query
        Parameters:
        api_key - String API Key
        localizedLat - Centralized Latitude, this will make it so that the search starts or is focused on that latitude first. An example would be if you set the localizedLat to a LosAngeles and query for "Paris", rather than it returning Paris, France, it will return Saint George Parish School, Ontario, CA, USA as that is closer and fits the Paris prefix.
        localizedLng - Centralized Longitude, this will make it so that the search starts or is focused on that latitude first. An example would be if you set the localizedLat to a LosAngeles and query for "Paris", rather than it returning Paris, France, it will return Saint George Parish School, Ontario, CA, USA as that is closer and fits the Paris prefix.
        searchQuery - Query to search
        Returns:
        MapzenPOJO

      • searchMapWithFilter

        @GET(value="/v1/autocomplete")
retrofit2.Call<MapzenPOJO> searchMapWithFilter(@Query(value="api_key")
                                                                               java.lang.String api_key,
                                                                               @Query(value="focus.point.lat")
                                                                               double localizedLat,
                                                                               @Query(value="focus.point.lon")
                                                                               double localizedLng,
                                                                               @Query(value="text")
                                                                               java.lang.String searchQuery,
                                                                               @Query(value="text")
                                                                               java.lang.String searchFilter)
        Search Map with an added filter (See below for filters)
        Parameters:
        api_key - String API Key
        localizedLat - Centralized Latitude, this will make it so that the search starts or is focused on that latitude first. An example would be if you set the localizedLat to a LosAngeles and query for "Paris", rather than it returning Paris, France, it will return Saint George Parish School, Ontario, CA, USA as that is closer and fits the Paris prefix.
        localizedLng - Centralized Longitude, this will make it so that the search starts or is focused on that latitude first. An example would be if you set the localizedLat to a LosAngeles and query for "Paris", rather than it returning Paris, France, it will return Saint George Parish School, Ontario, CA, USA as that is closer and fits the Paris prefix.
        searchQuery - Query to search
        searchFilter - The filter options include: -openstreetmap or osm -openaddresses or oa -geonames or gn -whosonfirst or wof Their details are covered here: https://mapzen.com/documentation/search/autocomplete/ Short explanation is, including 'oa' for a query of "Pennsylvania" will only return results that are on Pennsylvania ave, Pennsylvania st, etc. Exclude it and you could receive Pennsylvania, USA, or Pennsylvania Ave, Washington DC.
        Returns:
        MapzenPOJO

      • searchMapWithLayer

        @GET(value="/v1/autocomplete")
retrofit2.Call<MapzenPOJO> searchMapWithLayer(@Query(value="api_key")
                                                                              java.lang.String api_key,
                                                                              @Query(value="focus.point.lat")
                                                                              double localizedLat,
                                                                              @Query(value="focus.point.lon")
                                                                              double localizedLng,
                                                                              @Query(value="text")
                                                                              java.lang.String searchQuery,
                                                                              @Query(value="text")
                                                                              java.lang.String searchLayer)
        Search with a layer attached to narrow down results
        Parameters:
        api_key - String API Key
        localizedLat - Centralized Latitude, this will make it so that the search starts or is focused on that latitude first. An example would be if you set the localizedLat to a LosAngeles and query for "Paris", rather than it returning Paris, France, it will return Saint George Parish School, Ontario, CA, USA as that is closer and fits the Paris prefix.
        localizedLng - Centralized Longitude, this will make it so that the search starts or is focused on that latitude first. An example would be if you set the localizedLat to a LosAngeles and query for "Paris", rather than it returning Paris, France, it will return Saint George Parish School, Ontario, CA, USA as that is closer and fits the Paris prefix.
        searchQuery - Query to search
        searchLayer - Layer options for narrowing down results. List includes: -venue: points of interest, businesses, things with walls -address: places with a street address -street: streets,roads,highways -country: places that issue passports, nations, nation-states -macroregion: a related group of regions. Mostly in Europe -region: states and provinces -macrocounty: a related group of counties. Mostly in Europe. -county: official governmental area; usually bigger than a locality, almost always smaller than a region -locality: towns, hamlets, cities -localadmin: local administrative boundaries -borough: a local administrative boundary, currently only used for New York City -neighbourhood: social communities, neighbourhoods -coarse: alias for simultaneously using all administrative layers (everything except venue and address)
        Returns:
        MapzenPOJO
